**Brahma Purana (ब्रह्मपुराण)
[
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "नारायणं नमस्कृत्य नरं चैव नरोत्तमम् ।\nदेवीं सरस्वतीं चैव ततो जयमुदीरयेत् ॥",
    "transliteration": "nārāyaṇaṃ namaskṛtya naraṃ caiva narottamam | devīṃ sarasvatīṃ caiva tato jayam udīrayet ||",
    "translation_english": "Having bowed to Lord Nārāyaṇa, to Nara the supreme among men, and to Goddess Sarasvatī, one should then utter the word of victory."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "मैत्रेय उवाच |\nभगवन् ब्रह्मणः पुत्र कथयस्व महामुने |\nपुराणं ब्रह्मसंबद्धं सर्वपापप्रणाशनम् ||",
    "transliteration": "maitreya uvāca | bhagavan brahmaṇaḥ putra kathayasva mahāmune | purāṇaṃ brahma-sambaddhaṃ sarva-pāpa-praṇāśanam ||",
    "translation_english": "Maitreya said: O venerable sage, son of Brahmā, please narrate the Purāṇa connected with Brahmā, which destroys all sins."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूत उवाच |\nपुराणं ब्रह्मणः पुण्यं ब्रह्मलोकप्रदायकम् |\nवक्ष्यामि विधिवद् विप्राः शृणुध्वं संशितव्रताः ||",
    "transliteration": "sūta uvāca | purāṇaṃ brahmaṇaḥ puṇyaṃ brahma-loka-pradāyakam | vakṣyāmi vidhivad viprāḥ śṛṇudhvam saṃśita-vratāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Sūta said: I shall properly narrate the sacred Brahma Purāṇa, which bestows the abode of Brahmā. Listen attentively, O disciplined sages."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "यत्र सर्गश्च प्रलयः कल्पानां च विनिश्चयः |\nदेवानां च ऋषीणां च राज्ञां च वंशवर्णनम् ||",
    "transliteration": "yatra sargaś ca pralayaḥ kalpānāṃ ca viniścayaḥ | devānāṃ ca ṛṣīṇāṃ ca rājñāṃ ca vaṃśa-varṇanam ||",
    "translation_english": "In which are described creation and dissolution, the divisions of cosmic ages, and the genealogies of gods, sages, and kings."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मार्थकाममोक्षाणां सम्यग् ज्ञानप्रदर्शनम् |\nपुराणं ब्रह्मसंज्ञं तु श्रवणात् पापनाशनम् ||",
    "transliteration": "dharmārtha-kāma-mokṣāṇāṃ samyag jñāna-pradarśanam | purāṇaṃ brahma-saṃjñaṃ tu śravaṇāt pāpa-nāśanam ||",
    "translation_english": "This Brahma Purāṇa rightly expounds dharma, wealth, desire, and liberation, and merely hearing it destroys sins."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "यं ध्यायन्ति बुधाः समाधिसमये शुद्धं वियत्सन्निभम् ।",
    "transliteration": "yaṃ dhyāyanti budhāḥ samādhisamaye śuddhaṃ viyatsannibham ||",
    "translation_english": "One who meditates upon that in the state of samādhi, pure and resembling spacious stillness, ..."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "नित्यानन्दमयं प्रसन्नममलं सर्वेश्वरं निर्गुणम् ।",
    "transliteration": "nityānandamayaṃ prasannam amalaṃ sarveśvaraṃ nirguṇam ||",
    "translation_english": "…attains the eternal bliss, radiant and unblemished, the Lord of all, free from all qualities." 
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "यस्मात् सर्वमिदं प्रपञ्चरचितं मायाजगज्जायते ।",
    "transliteration": "yasmāt sarvam idaṃ prapañcaracitaṃ māyā jagajjāyate ||",
    "translation_english": "From which all this world, composed of the elements and the cosmic illusion, comes into being…" 
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "sanskrit_text": "यस्मिंस्तिष्ठति याति चान्तसमये कल्पानुकल्पे पुनः ।",
    "transliteration": "yasmiṃstiṣṭhati yāti ca anta-samaye kalpānukalpe punaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "…in which it abides and to which it returns at the end of the cosmic cycle and again at the start of the next." 
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "sanskrit_text": "यं ध्यात्वा मुनयः प्रपञ्चरहितं विन्दन्ति मोक्षं ध्रुवम् ।",
    "transliteration": "yaṃ dhyātvā munayaḥ prapañcaharitaṃ vindanti mokṣaṃ dhruvam ||",
    "translation_english": "Meditating upon that which is free from all manifestation, the sages attain unchanging liberation." 
  },
  
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "sanskrit_text": "सृष्टिस्थितिप्रलयहेतुभूतं त्रैलोक्यनाथं परमं प्रधानम् ।",
    "transliteration": "sṛṣṭi-sthiti-pralaya-hetu-bhūtaṃ trailokya-nāthaṃ paramaṃ pradhānam ||",
    "translation_english": "He is the supreme cause of creation, preservation, and dissolution, the sovereign Lord of the three worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "sanskrit_text": "अव्यक्तमव्ययं शान्तं सूक्ष्मात् सूक्ष्मतरं हरिम् ।",
    "transliteration": "avyaktam avyayaṃ śāntaṃ sūkṣmāt sūkṣmataraṃ harim ||",
    "translation_english": "He is unmanifest, imperishable, peaceful, subtler than the subtlest, and known as Hari."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "न यस्य जन्म कर्म वा न नामरूपविकल्पनम् ।",
    "transliteration": "na yasya janma karma vā na nāma-rūpa-vikalpanam ||",
    "translation_english": "He has neither birth nor action, nor distinctions of name and form."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "एक एव जगत्सर्वं व्याप्य तिष्ठति निर्गुणः ।",
    "transliteration": "eka eva jagat sarvaṃ vyāpya tiṣṭhati nirguṇaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "He alone pervades the entire universe, existing beyond all qualities."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "तमेव शरणं यान्ति ज्ञात्वा संसारभीरवः ।",
    "transliteration": "tam eva śaraṇaṃ yānti jñātvā saṃsāra-bhīravaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Knowing Him, those fearful of worldly existence seek Him alone as refuge."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "अविद्याग्रन्थिनिर्मुक्ता ज्ञानदीपप्रकाशिताः ।",
    "transliteration": "avidyā-granthi-nirmuktā jñāna-dīpa-prakāśitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Freed from the knots of ignorance, they are illumined by the lamp of knowledge."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "यस्य प्रसादमात्रेण मुच्यते जीवबन्धनात् ।",
    "transliteration": "yasya prasāda-mātreṇa mucyate jīva-bandhanāt ||",
    "translation_english": "By His grace alone, the soul is released from bondage."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "स ब्रह्मा स हरिः शक्रः स कालः स महेश्वरः ।",
    "transliteration": "sa brahmā sa hariḥ śakraḥ sa kālaḥ sa maheśvaraḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "He is Brahmā, He is Hari, He is Indra, He is Time, He is Mahēśvara."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "नान्यदस्ति परं तत्त्वं तस्मात्सर्वं प्रतिष्ठितम् ।",
    "transliteration": "nānyad asti paraṃ tattvaṃ tasmāt sarvaṃ pratiṣṭhitam ||",
    "translation_english": "There is no higher reality than Him; upon Him everything rests."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति ब्रह्मपुराणस्य प्रथमः परिच्छेद उच्यते ।",
    "transliteration": "iti brahma-purāṇasya prathamaḥ pariccheda ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus is declared the first chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },

  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्गं प्रथितं ब्रह्मणैव यत् सृष्टेः कारणं परमम्।",
    "transliteration": "sargaṃ prathitaṃ brahmaṇaiva yat sṛṣṭeḥ kāraṇaṃ paramam ||",
    "translation_english": "The creation was first declared by Brahmā, who is the supreme cause of all existence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्वं जगत्समाहितं तेनैव प्रजाप्यते।",
    "transliteration": "sarvaṃ jagat samāhitaṃ tenaiva prajāpyate ||",
    "translation_english": "All the worlds, organized and harmonious, are sustained through Him."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "अविद्यायाश्रयात्सर्वं मुञ्चति ज्ञानेनात्मनः।",
    "transliteration": "avidyāyāśrayātsarvaṃ muñcati jñānenātmanah ||",
    "translation_english": "All is freed from the bonds of ignorance through self-knowledge."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "शिवो हि प्रथमो देवः सृष्टेः संस्थापकः सदा।",
    "transliteration": "śivo hi prathamo devaḥ sṛṣṭeḥ sansthāpakaḥ sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "Shiva, the first deity, is always the establisher of creation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेजसा व्याप्य जगत्सर्वं ब्रह्मणि स्थितम्।",
    "transliteration": "tejasā vyāpya jagatsarvaṃ brahmaṇi sthitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Permeating all, the universe rests in the essence of Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्वभूतानां कारणं सदा परमं ध्रुवम्।",
    "transliteration": "sarvabhūtānāṃ kāraṇaṃ sadā paramaṃ dhruvam ||",
    "translation_english": "He is always the ultimate, fixed cause of all beings."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "विद्यया यः जानाति स मोक्षमार्गे गच्छति।",
    "transliteration": "vidyayā yaḥ jānāti sa mokṣamārge gacchati ||",
    "translation_english": "He who knows Him through knowledge walks the path of liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "कर्मणा ब्रह्मज्ञानेन मोक्षं लभते जनः।",
    "transliteration": "karmaṇā brahmajñānena mokṣaṃ labhate janaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "By action and knowledge of Brahmā, a person attains liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 9,
    "sanskrit_text": "सतां पथं गच्छन्ति ये ब्रह्मानुस्मरणेन।",
    "transliteration": "satāṃ pathaṃ gacchanti ye brahmānusmaraṇena ||",
    "translation_english": "Those who remember Brahmā follow the path of the virtuous."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 10,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं ब्रह्मपुराणस्य द्वितीयः परिच्छेद आरभ्यते।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ brahma-purāṇasya dvitīyaḥ pariccheda ārabhyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus begins the second chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 11,
    "sanskrit_text": "सृष्टेः प्रथमे कर्मण्याः ब्रह्मज्ञानेन लभ्यते।",
    "transliteration": "sṛṣṭeḥ prathame karmaṇyāḥ brahmajñānena labhyate ||",
    "translation_english": "In the beginning of creation, actions are guided and understood through the knowledge of Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 12,
    "sanskrit_text": "भूतानां च कारणं ब्रह्म तत्वे प्रतिष्ठितम्।",
    "transliteration": "bhūtānāṃ ca kāraṇaṃ brahma tattve pratiṣṭhitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Brahmā is established as the cause of all beings in essence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "जगत्सर्वं च व्याप्य ब्रह्मणि स्थितम् यथार्थतः।",
    "transliteration": "jagatsarvaṃ ca vyāpya brahmaṇi sthitam yathārthataḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The entire universe pervades Brahmā and truly rests in Him."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "ज्ञानेन कर्मसु मोक्षं लभते प्रजापतिर्नरः।",
    "transliteration": "jñānena karmasu mokṣaṃ labhate prajāpati-naraḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Through knowledge in action, a human attains liberation, O Lord of Creatures."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "सतां मार्गं गच्छन्ति ये ब्रह्मनिष्ठा पथे।",
    "transliteration": "satāṃ mārgaṃ gacchanti ye brahma-niṣṭhā pathe ||",
    "translation_english": "Those who are devoted to Brahmā follow the path of the virtuous."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "अविद्यया जडता सर्वं बाधते प्रजायते।",
    "transliteration": "avidyayā jaḍatā sarvaṃ bādhate prajāyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Through ignorance, all beings are bound and suffer in worldly existence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "ज्ञानादेव मोक्षमार्गः प्रकटते जगतां हितम्।",
    "transliteration": "jñānādeva mokṣamārgaḥ prakaṭate jagatāṃ hitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Only through knowledge does the path of liberation reveal itself, for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "कर्मफलत्यागात् मुक्तः स्यात् ज्ञानेन च परां गतिम्।",
    "transliteration": "karmaphalatyāgāt muktaḥ syāt jñānena ca parāṃ gatim ||",
    "translation_english": "By renouncing the fruits of actions and through knowledge, one attains the supreme goal."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्त्वरजस्तमः गुणाः संसारसागरमुत्सृज्यते।",
    "transliteration": "sattvarajas-tamaḥ guṇāḥ saṃsārasāgaramutṛjyate ||",
    "translation_english": "The qualities of goodness, passion, and ignorance, when transcended, lead one out of the ocean of worldly existence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं ब्रह्मपुराणस्य द्वितीयस्य अध्यायः समाप्तः।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ brahma-purāṇasya dvitīyasya adhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the second chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 21,
    "sanskrit_text": "सदाचारैः पुण्येनैव मनुष्यः शुद्धिमाप्नोति।",
    "transliteration": "sadācāraiḥ puṇyenaiva manuṣyaḥ śuddhim āpnoti ||",
    "translation_english": "Through virtuous conduct and merits, a human attains purity."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 22,
    "sanskrit_text": "योगेन ब्रह्मसन्निधानं प्राप्य मोक्षमार्गं गतः।",
    "transliteration": "yogena brahma-sannidhānaṃ prāpya mokṣamārgaṃ gataḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Through yoga, one reaches the presence of Brahmā and proceeds on the path of liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 23,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्यं ब्रह्मसम्बन्धं च साधकस्य कार्यसिद्धये।",
    "transliteration": "satyaṃ brahma-sambandhaṃ ca sādhakasya kārya-siddhaye ||",
    "translation_english": "Truth and connection with Brahmā ensure the success of a practitioner’s spiritual efforts."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 24,
    "sanskrit_text": "अविद्यायाः वशीभूता नरकं प्राप्नोति प्रजाः।",
    "transliteration": "avidyāyāḥ vaśībhūtā narakaṃ prāpnoti prajāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Controlled by ignorance, beings fall into suffering and bondage."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 25,
    "sanskrit_text": "ज्ञानसंपन्नः पुरुषो ब्रह्मलोकं प्राप्नोति च।",
    "transliteration": "jñāna-sampannaḥ puruṣo brahma-lokaṃ prāpnoti ca ||",
    "translation_english": "A person endowed with knowledge attains the world of Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 26,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्येन च धर्मेणैव जीवः मुक्तिमाप्नोति।",
    "transliteration": "satyena ca dharmeṇaiva jīvaḥ muktim āpnoti ||",
    "translation_english": "Through truthfulness and righteous conduct, the soul attains liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 27,
    "sanskrit_text": "व्रजति नित्यं धर्ममार्गे सिद्धिं लभते नरः।",
    "transliteration": "vrajati nityaṃ dharma-mārge siddhiṃ labhate naraḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "A person who constantly follows the path of righteousness achieves perfection."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 2,
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 28,
